Durban - The Brighton Beach police Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit is making an appeal to members of the community to assist with regards to the whereabouts of a man pictured in the identikit. He is believed to be in his late 30's and can assist in the investigation of a rape case. He is of medium built and was wearing a blue shirt. It is alleged that on 2 May 2019 at 20:25, a 52-year-old woman was raped and robbed next to a church in Old Mission Road, Bluff. Since then police have been searching for possible leads to solve the case. A case of rape and common robbery was opened for investigation. Anyone with information of his whereabouts is requested to contact Detective Constable Bouverie at the Brighton Beach FCS Unit on 031 451 8059/ 081 046 3162 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111. Daily News